        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 3:55PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 355 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Tyrone, or 20 miles north of Trinidad, moving east at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tyrone and Model.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
